column5: My next door neighbor puts out feed for the deer when the snow flies and every morning and evening I have anywhere from 1 to as many as 17 deer in my backyard and I've had deer as close as 10' from my back deck.  I have a trail starting at the back of my property that meanders 1/2 a mile thru the bush out to hwy 28 and alot of them come down there, but they also come along the dirt road in front of the house and come up my driveway.  Pretty kool to be sitting here at the puter looking out the window and have a herd of deer walking down the road only 100' away  Here's a couple pics I took earlier today when it was still fairly dark out and snowing but you can get the idea.
You are a very lucky man Lew. We get rabbits and raccons, and that keeps my dogs in good shape
Lew found a piece of paradise!  when can i move in?
Lew, are you having venison roast for Christmas?
Hey skeets !!! I have waskawy wabbits !!! do they count.
Very cool Lew, your lucky to have that in your back yard.  Views like that in the morning make it all worth while moving to the country.
Fantastic Lew! Sounds like your loving your new digs.
That would be real nice to wake up to Lew, you're a lucky man  Joey
I have a doe tag still to be filled....wanna split?
You are very lucky Lew.... must be very relaxing, watching from your vantage point Thanks for sharing those pics!!! Leechman

The joys of country livin' eh Lew ?  How about your wife?...Is she getting used to it ?...  Maribeth was not too enthused in the beginning but now she has lots of friends (quilting and basket weaving) and is active at the Settlers Village in town...not so remote now it seems...
VEry nice Lew, what does Marvin think of them?  Maureen
You picked a great location Lew.
